Everytime there's a global event  human lives adapt. No difference with this covid 19 Pandemic.
this pandemic caused the entire media entertainment market shift.
from events cancellation   global sports cancellation  i doubt cinemas can last much longer.
the shift has made a lot of profits for streaming businesses and human are moving towards that paradigm.
I went to read up about how cinemas make money globally and it is interesting that a lot of them are only making money through the condiments and not sale of tickets

meaning in States where hollywood is  all the movies are screen for "free" by the cinemas. all the tickets profit will go to the movie makers. the cinemas will "lend" their venues out and make money through condiments sold like popcorn  drinks  etc.
in SG  smaller countries  cinemas "buy" the movie and make profit from ticket sales (proportion) and condiments
